## Part 1 — Plan Your Instance Map

Before touching AWS, decide your friendly names. Rules:

- lowercase, no spaces (they become Discord dropdown choices)
- `all` is **reserved** — never use it as an instance name
- max **24 instances** if you want dropdown choices (Discord's limit is 25 choices; `all` takes one slot)

This JSON goes into a Lambda env var later — **each instance carries its own region**:

```json
{
  "gameserver": {"id": "i-0aaa1111111111111", "region": "ap-south-1"},
  "devbox":     {"id": "i-0bbb2222222222222", "region": "us-east-1"},
  "gitlab":     {"id": "i-0ccc3333333333333", "region": "eu-west-1"}
}
```

Also decide **schedule groups** (region doesn't matter here — that's the whole point):

| Group | Instances | Schedule |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `weekday-9to9` | gameserver, devbox | Mon–Fri 9AM–9PM |
| `always-on` | gitlab | never auto-stopped |

