### Lambda General Settings

**Configuration → General Configuration:** Timeout **10 seconds**, Memory **128 MB**.

> ⚠️ **Discord's hard limit is 3 seconds** for the initial response. Start/Stop/Reboot return instantly (async on AWS side). Status queries run one `DescribeInstances` per region sequentially — with 2–4 regions you're comfortably under 3s. If you ever run 6+ regions or dozens of instances, switch to deferred responses (interaction type 5 + follow-up webhook).

