## Part 7 — Register Slash Commands

Create `register.py` on your PC:

```python
import requests

BOT_TOKEN      = "YOUR_BOT_TOKEN"
APPLICATION_ID = "YOUR_APPLICATION_ID"
GUILD_ID       = "YOUR_SERVER_ID"

# Must match INSTANCE_MAP keys in Lambda, plus "all"
INSTANCES = ["gameserver", "devbox", "gitlab", "all"]

name_option = {
    "name": "name",
    "description": "Which instance to target",
    "type": 3,          # STRING
    "required": True,
    "choices": [{"name": i, "value": i} for i in INSTANCES],
}

commands = [
    {"name": "start-ec2",  "description": "Start an EC2 instance",           "options": [name_option]},
    {"name": "stop-ec2",   "description": "Stop an EC2 instance",            "options": [name_option]},
    {"name": "reboot-ec2", "description": "Reboot an EC2 instance",          "options": [name_option]},
    {"name": "status-ec2", "description": "Status: state, IP, uptime, cost", "options": [name_option]},
]

url = f"https://discord.com/api/v10/applications/{APPLICATION_ID}/guilds/{GUILD_ID}/commands"
headers = {"Authorization": f"Bot {BOT_TOKEN}"}

for cmd in commands:
    r = requests.post(url, headers=headers, json=cmd)
    print(f"{cmd['name']}: {r.status_code}", "" if r.ok else r.text)
```

Run:

```bash
pip install requests
python register.py
```

Expected: four lines of `201` (or `200` when re-registering — both are success).

> 💡 Discord allows max **25 choices** per option. More than 24 instances? Remove `choices` entirely — the option becomes free-text and Lambda-side validation still rejects bad names with a helpful list. Names stay region-agnostic, so `register.py` never needs region info.

